dataIdInfo.idAbs: This line data layer represents roads for Juneau County, Wisconsin in 2017. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Juneau_Roads_2017.gdb.[Roads data contain the centerlines of all the roads in the county. They are coded by class being: 5 - Interstates, 4 - US Highways, 3 - State Highways, 2 - County Trunk Roads, 1 - Town/Local Roads and 0 - Private Roads, Trails or Alleys. They also have an address range assigned to them with a right and left to and from range, the centerlines broken down into segments with what community (zipcode) they are in, and also what emergency zone (ESN) they fall in.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.
dataIdInfo.idCredit:
Juneau County Land Information
[Roads data of Juneau County were initially created using the US Census TIGER file. They were then reprojected to Juneau County coordinates. Edits by the Juneau County Land Information Office for the addition of new roads were done. 2003 & 2010 aerial photographs and new survey maps were used to help with the edits]
